<title>PORTUGAL: Strike-hit Portugal mine has copper for least week.</title>
<headline>Strike-hit Portugal mine has copper for least week.</headline>
<dateline>LISBON 1997-07-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>The strike-hit Portuguese copper mine Neves Corvo would only need to start warning clients that they could face delivery problems after a week of stoppage, a company spokesman told Reuters on Tuesday.</p>
<p>Personnel director Raul Araujo could give no figure for the current level of stocks.</p>
<p>Miners at the 107,000-tonne per year mine began a strike on Monday over company plans to introduce seven-day shift working.</p>
<p>Araujo said that after the first week, the reduction of deliveries would be a gradual process with no immediate declaration of force majeure.</p>
<p>--Lisbon bureau 3511-3150035</p>
